              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p35h7cd9n/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>informing me that <persName>Rev M N Nathan</persName> had <sic>voluntary</sic><lb/>\n                resigned his office as minister, and requesting me to<lb/> inform <persName>Dr\n                    Eckman</persName> of this fact and to invite him<lb/> to <del>become a\n                    candidate</del> apply for the situation<lb/> as <sic>If</sic> they can procure a\n                minister without advertising<lb/> they would prefer it no reason being assigned<lb/>\n                for the resignation of <persName>Mr Nathan</persName>. <persName>Dr\n                    Eckman</persName><lb/> has written to <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> to know\n                from him<lb/> whether his resignation is permanent or whether<lb/> he would again\n                resume office if matters were<lb/> accommodated to him, as he would not\n                interrupt<lb/> or make application, without he first <hi rend=\"underline\">was\n                    certain</hi><lb/> of this fact. Should such be the case, and<lb/> you do not\n                intend to apply, your influence <add>?</add><lb/> the President <persName>S\n                    Kursheet</persName> might have some weight<lb/> to induce them to accept him, I\n                take it for granted<lb/> that they have not <hi rend=\"underline\">offered</hi> you\n                the situation as my<lb/> letter is from one of the Trustees. <persName>Mr Myer\n                    Simpson</persName></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I should like to see the Doctor in a proper position<lb/> when his\n                usefulness could be made available,<lb/> the more I see and know of him the more\n                impressed<lb/> I am with the importance of his mission to\n                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>.<lb/> He is preparing a continuation of his\n                article for<lb/> the Occident <hi rend=\"underline\">save room</hi> for it it will be\n                on in a<lb/> few days.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><sic>remember</sic> me to our friend <persName>S.S.</persName> and\n                Lady and<lb/> all friends. I intended to have written more but<lb/> I am called of.\n                Yours Sincerely</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">S N Carvalho</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p><persName>Sarah</persName> regards to you</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p35h7cd9n/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
